<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Salinas Praises Candidates' Debate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salinas Praises Candidates' Debate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1505022494 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 2057 GMT 13 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1505022494 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Veracruz, 13 May (Notimex) -- President Carlos 
Salinas de Gortari said here today that the debate among the 
country's three leading political forces "is a big step forward 
in Mexico's democratic life." "We have experienced a genuine 
shift toward plurality. This shift, which is worth 
consolidating, is the result of electoral reforms that the 
country's various political forces have effected through 
dialogue," he said. 
  After closing in this Gulf of Mexico port the Second Forum 
on 
Financing and Investment Opportunities for the Southeast, 
Salinas said the confrontation "reveals our country's new 
political culture." 
  Presidential candidates Ernesto Zedillo of the Institutional 
Revolutionary Party [PRI], Cuauthemoc Cardenas of the Democratic 
Revolutionary Party [PRD], and Diego Fernandez of the National 
Action Party [PAN] presented their political platforms on 
Thursday night. 
  Of this debate, which was held in Mexico for the first time, 
Salinas said: "We can declare that the electoral process in 
Mexico is not discriminating. Quite the contrary, it is 
all-embracing." He added: "There is room for everyone in the 
country's legal framework." Salinas said the candidates spoke 
freely and voiced without restriction their opinions and 
proposals so they can be considered and assessed by the Mexican 
people. "From now on, everyone should obey the law and the 
Mexican people's electoral will," he finally said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

