<H3> <TI>   Central Bank Blamed for Currency Decline </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Central Bank Blamed for Currency Decline </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1605040394 Caracas Union Radio Network in Spanish 2200 GMT 
15 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1605040394 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Union Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Union Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Conflict over the mechanisms implemented to end the 
fall of the bolivar against the dollar continues. While the 
Economic Cabinet has blamed the Central Bank of Venezuela for 
the ineffectiveness of the measures applied in this regard, 
Central Bank President Antonio Casas Gonzalez recalled that the 
mechanisms for intervening in the banks was evaluated and 
accepted by the executive branch. 
  Additionally, there are differences over control exchanges 
between Finance Minister Julio Sosa Rodriguez and Asdrubal 
Batista, minister for reforming the national economy. In this 
regard, Casas Gonzalez admitted that the auction of foreign 
currency will not resolve in itself the expectations of the 
public but that this would depend on the policies on banking, 
fiscal, and public order problems that convey credibility to the 
community. 

</TEXT>

