<F P=100> Uruguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spanish Courts Request Questioning of Detained Basques </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spanish Courts Request Questioning of Detained Basques </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1605154794 Montevideo EL OBSERVADOR ECONOMICO in Spanish 
10 May 94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PY1605154794 </F>
<F P=104>  Montevideo EL OBSERVADOR ECONOMICO </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Spanish courts yesterday sent to the Uruguayan 
courts a rogatory letter so that the detained Basques might be 
interrogated on incidents linked to the cases that prompted 
their extradition petitions. 
  The Spanish courts' petition has prompted a new controversy 
at the judicial branch level, as the interrogatories must 
include all Basque citizens who are allegedly ETA [Basque 
Homeland and Liberty] members, whether or not their extradition 
has been approved. 
  One of the cases included in the petition was approved, and 
this elicited a reaction from the defense attorneys of those 
involved. 
  Attorney Gustavo Puig has filed remedies of appeal and 
appeals for annulment. The legal issue now will therefore have 
to be resolved by the Court of Criminal Appeals. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

