<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-LAT-94-096 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  16 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defeated PMDB Candidate Supports Lula </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defeated PMDB Candidate Supports Lula </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1605224294 Rio de Janeiro O GLOBO in Portuguese 16 May 94 
p 7 </F>

<F P=103> PY1605224294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro O GLOBO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Curitiba -- In the wake of his defeat at the PMDB 
[Brazilian Democratic Movement Party] primaries, former Parana 
Governor Roberto Requiao yesterday announced that he will 
endorse Workers Party [PT] candidate Luis Inacio Lula da Silva. 
Requiao said he is convinced Lula will win the elections in the 
first round. Requiao conceded defeat to Quercia yesterday 
morning in a speech he delivered before PMDB delegates at the 
Legislative Assembly in Curitiba. 
  Requiao said: Lula will win because the other parties are 
increasingly demoralized. At the PMDB convention, we run the 
risk of internally promoting the rehabilitation of Deputies 
Genabaldo Correa, Ibsen Pinheiro, and Manuel Moreira, who were 
charged by the Budget CPI [Congressional Investigating 
Committee]. 
  Without directly attacking Quercia, Requiao reaffirmed that 
he will not participate in the PMDB campaign. 
  Requiao said: I said I would do without with Quercia's 
support for my candidacy and I hope he will do the same. I 
support Lula. No one can prevent me from seeking a Senate seat. 
  Requiao made it clear that he will not hold the PMDB rank 
and 
file responsible for the outcome of the elections. 
  Requiao said: PMDB members cannot be held responsible; that 
lies with the slow, weak leaders who adopted an ostrich-like 
policy in Congress by sticking their heads in the sand. He 
stated that he will continue within the PMDB. 

</TEXT>

