<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Rules Out Real-Dollar Conversion Mechanism </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Rules Out Real-Dollar Conversion Mechanism </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1705135094 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in 
Portuguese 1000 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1705135094 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Finance Minister Rubens Ricupero has ruled out the 
possibility of the government converting the real in dollars or 
in other currencies. He declined, however, to make comments on 
the exchange rate. 
  The minister said savings accounts will not be modified, and 
that they will continue to be adjusted by the TR [Reference 
Interest Rate]. He did not identify, however, the factors that 
will be taken into account for calculating the TR. 
  Ricupero announced that this week he will set the rules for 
conversion of school monthly fees into real value units. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

