<F P=100> SOUTH AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   Start of Mercosur `Postponed for 3 Months' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Start of Mercosur `Postponed for 3 Months' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1605213194 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1714 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1605213194 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 16 May (NA) -- The Economy Ministry 
press office has reported that Economy Minister Domingo Cavallo 
announced in the ROK on 16 May that the launch of the Mercosur 
[Common Market of the South] free trade zone will be postponed 
for three months. 
  The press office issued a communique to inform the public 
about Cavallo's agenda in that Asian country. It states that the 
head of the Economy Ministry "asserted that the Mercosur will 
function like a free trade zone as of 1 April 1995 and that a 
customs union will be established later." 
  The free trade zone between Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay, and 
Uruguay was scheduled to come into effect on 1 January 1995. 

</TEXT>

