<H3> <TI>   PRC Delegation Meets With Agriculture Officials </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PRC Delegation Meets With Agriculture Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1405034094 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1517 GMT 10 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1405034094 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 10 May (NOTIMEX) -- Agrarian Reform 
Under Secretary Gustavo Gordillo de Anda exchanged information 
and experiences on agrarian topics with a Chinese delegation led 
by Agriculture Vice Minister Liu Chengguo. 
  In the meeting, the goal of which was to strengthen 
bilateral 
relations, they analyzed cooperation for various programs and 
projects to help rural producers. Gordillo de Anda stressed 
that President Carlos Salinas de Gortari has paid special 
attention to the rural sector through the reforms of 
Constitutional Article 27 and the new agrarian law. 
  Chengguo said his country is taking several actions to 
overcome the crisis in the countryside, including the 
elimination of the commune system and the organization of 
cooperatives that will permit the development of the Chinese 
countryside. He said his country views exchange and cooperation 
with Mexico as important because its experience in investment, 
support, and autonomy for peasants is valuable and will be 
useful for China. 
  The members of the Chinese delegation met with the heads of 
the Agrarian Prosecutor's Office and the National Agrarian 
Registry [Registro Agrario Nacional -- RAN], with whom they 
exchanged viewpoints on the Procede [expansion unknown] and RAN 
programs. 
  The meeting was also attended by Senior Officer Raul Pineda 
Pineda, Agrarian Organization Director Ricardo Chavez Perez, and 
Rosalia Enciso of the Foreign Secretariat. 

</TEXT>

