<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fujimori Meets Romania's Vacaroiu, Holds News Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fujimori Meets Romania's Vacaroiu, Holds News Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1705214794 Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network in 
Spanish 1800 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1705214794 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Alberto Fujimori held a 45-minute meeting 
with Romanian Prime Minister Nicolae Vacaroiu in Government 
House today. After the private protocol meeting, President 
Fujimori gave a news conference to Romanian reporters. This is 
part of the news conference. [passage indistinct] 
  The news conference given by the president to the Romanian 
reporters referred mainly to two issues: Andean integration and 
foreign debt. President Fujimori also said the Romanian 
official's visit will help develop electric energy in Peru. He 
added that Romania has long experience in electrical power, 
especially hydroelectric and thermoelecric plants. Fujimori said 
that in the last five years important steps have been taken for 
Andean integration, although he noted there are still barriers 
that can be overcome united. This is part of the news conference 
given by President Fujimori to the Romanian reporters who are 
part of the delegation headed by Romanian Prime Minister Nicolae 
Vacaroiu. 

</TEXT>

