<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bomb Destroys Bank Branch in Santiago </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bomb Destroys Bank Branch in Santiago </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1605213894 Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional in Spanish 1800 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1605213894 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A Bhif Bank branch was damaged by a bomb last night. 
Those responsible for the attack are reportedly members of the 
MIR [Movement of the Revolutionary Left]. 
  [Begin unidentified reporter recording] The tranquility of 
Sunday night was abruptly interrupted when a powerful bomb 
exploded at the Bhif Bank branch on Macul Street near the corner 
of Irarrazaval Streets. An area of 100 meters, including nearby 
houses, was damaged. Fortunately, there were no casualties. 
According to preliminary information, the explosion was caused 
by a plastic bomb with a high destructive power. The bank branch 
was considerably damaged. Unofficial reports state that an 
extremist organization is responsible for the attack. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

