<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Samper Charges Pastrana Refuses To Debate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1705134194 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network in 
Spanish 1200 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1705134194 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Letter from Colombian Liberal Party presidential candidate </F>
Ernesto Samper Pizano to Dario Arizmendi, news director of 
Caracol Network on the cancellation of the scheduled 
presidential debate; date of letter not given] 
  [Text] Dear Dario: Last week, Conservative Party 
presidential candidate Andres Pastrana sent a message to the 
media in which he tried to schedule a program of debates 
specifying the topics, participants, and hours of the debates 
among the presidential and vice presidential candidates. Within 
this timeframe, a debate was scheduled for tomorrow in Cadena 
Caracol studios on the topic of farming. 
  Subsequently, Dr. Pastrana sent a message expressing his 
refusal to participate in the debate proposed by himself. I 
deplore the situation created by this inconsistency, which has 
occurred previously in responses by Dr. Pastrana to other media 
proposals. 
  Consequently, I believe that none of the meetings proposed 
for tomorrow in Caracol studios will be held. This, however, 
does not preclude their being rescheduled in the future. Please 
receive a cordial greeting. 
  [signed] Ernesto Samper Pizano. 

</TEXT>

