<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   People's Government Leader on Delegates' Reports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    People's Government Leader on Delegates' Reports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1605224994 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1935 GMT 
16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1605224994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Humberto Rodriguez Gonzalez, president of the 
People's Government in Santa Clara, has stated that the current 
process in which delegates present progress reports to their 
voters has begun in Villa Clara Province and is going well. 
Rodriguez said that the idea of backing the measures approved by 
the national parliament has prevailed at the meetings, and that 
the delegates are well-prepared, fully informed on every matter 
concerning the population, in an effort to find solutions, or at 
least study the causes, of the difficulties. 
  The Santa Clara Administrative Council has agreed to begin 
having locally run enterprises reflect upon application of and 
compliance with the policy of (?cadres), very particularly those 
things having to do with workers' living standards. For this 
latter, an overall program will be formulated that will 
encourage an administrative leader to feel like one of the 
workers, but with greater responsibilities. 

</TEXT>

