<DOCNO> FBIS4-57399 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat095_a_94005" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-LAT-94-095 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  16 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   CTC Assemblies Process To Continue Through June </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CTC Assemblies Process To Continue Through June </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1605230594 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1932 GMT 
16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1605230594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The subject of economic efficiency at each 
individual work center is at the heart of the discussions in the 
assemblies process being massively held by the CTC [Cuban 
Workers Federation] and its unions, as of today, in the same 
spirit as the recently held Parliaments in the Workplace. These 
assemblies began last month as pilot assemblies and will 
continue through the month of June, with the objective of 
avoiding marathons and favoring proper preparation of these 
meetings, which should be open and free of preconceived outlines. 
  The national leadership of the CTC has told its unions to be 
demanding regarding administrative reports, which may not 
contain justifications, but must instead be very objective about 
what needs be done at the work center to (?prioritize) 
difficulties and achieve efficiency. (?To begin) the assemblies, 
last Monday's [9 May] TRABAJADORES editorial will be read. That 
editorial is about this process. 

</TEXT>

