<H3> <TI>   Colombian Navy Flagship Visits Havana </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Colombian Navy Flagship Visits Havana </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1805184494 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1805184494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Marieta Cabrera] </F>
  [Text] At 0900 on 18 May, the ARC [expansion unknown] 
Gloria, flagship of the Colombian Navy, which is visiting Cuba 
for a second time, put in at the port of the Cuban Revolutionary 
Navy's [MGR] General Staff. The crew, headed by Captain (Eduardo 
Otero Erazo), was greeted by Colombian Ambassador Ricardo 
Santamaria and Captain (Martin Jodar), chief of the MGR General 
Staff, who welcomed the ship to Cuban territory. Over the past 
25 years, this Colombian Navy ship has visited 48 countries on 
five continents. Cuba is the second stop in this year's 
eight-nation tour which began with Kingston, Jamaica. 
  As regards the ship's goals, the ship's captain said the 
following: 
  [Begin recording] [(Otero)] I believe it is going to be a 
very interesting visit, which will serve to further reaffirm the 
ties of friendship and fraternity that exist between the peoples 
of Colombia and Cuba. 
  [Cabrera] Why was Cuba selected? 
  [(Otero)] I believe Cuba was selected because it is one of 
the most important cultures in Latin America, and also to 
reaffirm the ties of friendship between the two countries. [end 
recording] 
  The flagship's crew met with Rear Admiral Pedro Perez 
Betancourt, chief of the MGR, who expressed to the Colombian 
crew the interest the Revolutionary Armed Forces [FAR] minister 
and the chief of the General Staff have in this visit. He also 
discussed the naval history of the two nations and weather 
conditions en route to Cuba. 
  During their stay, the visitors will have a busy agenda 
which 
includes meeting members of the FAR and the population in 
general while the ship is open to visitors. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

