<H3> <TI>   Chilean Socialists Seek Diplomatic Ties With Havana </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chilean Socialists Seek Diplomatic Ties With Havana </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1905014994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1905014994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Congressmen of the ruling [as heard] Socialist Party 
of Chile have asked Chilean President Eduardo Frei to 
reestablish diplomatic relations with Cuba, which have been 
severed for more than 20 years. 
  Deputy Anibal Perez [as heard], who spoke on behalf of those 
Chilean congressmen, referred to the level of development 
achieved between the two countries following the resumption of 
consular and commercial ties in 1991. 
  According to the socialist congressmen, over the past three 
years and within a climate of rapprochement, Chilean businessmen 
have invested more than $20 million in Cuba, while 11,000 
Chilean tourists traveled to Cuba last year. The Socialist Party 
of Chile is the main ally of President Frei's ruling Christian 
Democratic Party. 

</TEXT>

