<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   People's Councils To Support New Medications Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    People's Councils To Support New Medications Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1705120094 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1705120094 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today the presidents of the 102 People's Councils of 
the city of Havana analyzed the support these organizations are 
to provide in monitoring the new national medications program 
that will go into in effect as of tomorrow in this capital. 
Provincial health director Dr. Pastor Castell explained that 
this plan seeks to gradually ensure that the necessary medicines 
are physically supplied by the medical-pharmaceutical industry, 
to perfect distribution, and to link every welfare institution 
to a particular pharmacy. Castell explained that the success of 
the new program also depends on knowing in advance what 
medicines these pharmacies have and, in keeping with this, 
prescribing those medicines to one's patients. Castell said that 
among the plan's objectives are to get the medications to 
whoever really needs them and to have the population feel 
satisfied. The plan will also combat speculation or illegal 
sales of medicines that are in short supply. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

