<H3> <TI>   Military Industries To Help National Economy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Industries To Help National Economy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1905002394 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1905002394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In a news conference, Brigadier General Luis Perez, 
chief of the Military Industries Union, UIM [Union de Industrias 
Militares], reported that this year the UIM will earmark 28 
percent of its production for the national economy. Gen. Perez 
added that in 1993, the UIM allotted 25 percent of its 
production to the internal market and it intends to contribute 
40 percent of its production in 1995. 
  He explained that in the past, the UIM had only provided 
service to the Armed Forces, but that due to the current 
difficulties, it has decided to help the national economy. 
These industries manufacture carts for sugarcane transport, 
cutting tools, agricultural appliances, wheelbarrows, 
compressors, and other items in great demand. 

</TEXT>

