<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Marianao Gas Plant Breakdown Disrupts Normal Service </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Marianao Gas Plant Breakdown Disrupts Normal Service </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1805153194 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1404 GMT 
18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1805153194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana's Manufactured Gas Enterprise has announced 
that due to a breakdown at the Marianao gas plant, service was 
limited on 17 May. The gas company also announced that this 
situation will continue until noon on 19 May, and apologizes for 
the inconvenience to the population. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

