<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Power Plant Generator To Undergo Maintenance </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Power Plant Generator To Undergo Maintenance </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1805132894 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1100 
GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1805132894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Progreso Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Generator unit No. 6 at the Diez de Octubre power 
plant in Nuevitas is being dismantled for general maintenance. A 
total of 337 workers will participate in this task, which will 
take 20 days. Afterwards, they will continue with the repairs to 
the air-preheating system, change the air ducts, and install a 
forced-air fan and a seawater pump. 
  The maintenance is scheduled to be done within 70 work 
shifts, but the workers expect to conclude it in 60, as they did 
before, with generator unit No. 5. Once the maintenance work is 
completed, generator unit No. 6 will produce 110 megawatt-hours, 
in contrast to the mere 45 megawatt-hours currently being 
produced. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

