<H3> <TI>   Varadero Beach Tourism Convention Opens 17 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Varadero Beach Tourism Convention Opens 17 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1705185894 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1705185894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The 15th Cuba-94 Tourism Convention was inaugurated 
on 17 May at Varadero Beach, Matanzas Province. There are 88 
tourism companies participating. Boris Reyes, president of the 
organizing committee, gave the opening address: 
  [Begin Reyes recording] We hope that each one of you 
fulfills 
the promotional and commercial aspects of your trip to Cuba and 
that your stay at the beautiful blue beach of Varadero will be 
gratifying as well as unforgettable. [end recording] 
  Important foreign associations, hoteliers, journalists, 
businessmen, and personalities of the tourism industry have come 
to the convention to exchange experiences, explore Cuba's 
tourist product, and complete negotiations that will benefit 
Cuba's economy. 
  The event will also serve to introduce the publications 
(SECCIONES) and GRANMA INTERNATIONAL, in German, to the Ministry 
of Tourism's Puerto Sol, Isla Azul, and Horizontes hotel chains. 
  Tourism Minister Osmany Cienfuegos, Politburo member Yadira 
Garcia, and other personalities of the tourist industry were 
present at the convention's opening. 

