<H3> <TI>   Jonassaint Urges National Reconciliation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jonassaint Urges National Reconciliation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1805195394 Paris AFP in Spanish 1825 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1805195394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Port-au-Prince, 18 May (AFP) -- Provisional 
President Emile Jonassaint (who is not recognized by the 
international community) asked Haitians on Wednesday to rally 
around the national flag and reconcile themselves "as brothers 
of the same nation." 
  In a radio and television message broadcast to the nation on 
18 May on the occasion of Flag Day and of the University of 
Haiti [as received], Jonassaint said the "union of the (Haitian) 
people is as necessary now as it was during the conquest for 
independence." He also urged Haitians, at a time when 
"consciences are being manipulated, to receive the legacy of our 
ancestors" and "hoist the flag before the people" and "protect 
its honor." 
  Prime Minister Robert Malval, who was forced to resign (and 
is recognized by the international community), asked students 
earlier at the same celebration not to allow "force to be more 
important than the law." Malval, in the presence of the 
diplomatic corps that went to his house to offer support, 
reiterated (?his rejection of) Jonassaint's "illegal" regime. 

</TEXT>

