<F P=106> [From the "This Morning" Newscast] </F>
  [Text] President Violeta Barrios de Chamorro today toured 
several municipalities in Masaya and Rivas where she inaugurated 
several judicial offices in San Juan de Oriente, Diria, Potosi, 
[word indistinct], and San Jorge. 
  At the end of her working tour, in San Jorge, President 
Chamorro spoke to the accompanying reporters and told them that 
the military bill will be presented to the Nicaraguan parliament 
today. 
  She also said that the list of three candidates for the 
Supreme Court justice position will be sent to the National 
Assembly this week. 
  Referring to the constitutional reforms, the president said 
that they are being studied and stressed that she wants true 
reforms, not a constituent assembly. 
  She was categorical in stating that lay education will 
continue and will remain unchanged; consequently, people cannot 
be asked to change their minds. 

