<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Supports Former Venezuelan President Perez </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Supports Former Venezuelan President Perez </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1905035294 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 2113 GMT 18 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1905035294 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Managua, 18 May (NOTIMEX) -- An official source has 
reported that Nicaraguan President Violeta Chamorro today 
contacted former Venezuelan President Carlos Andres Perez to 
express her solidarity with him. A Presidency document states 
"Chamorro contacted Perez this morning to express her solidarity 
with and fondness for him." 
  The Venezuelan Supreme Court of Justice issued today in 
Caracas an arrest warrant for the former president as part of 
his trial for allegedly embezzling $17 million between 1989 and 
1992. The Presidency communique recalled a message by Perez in 
which he said he "never" embezzled the secret $17 million fund, 
part of which reportedly was transferred to the current 
Nicaraguan Government to "reinforce democracy." Perez was 
impeached on 20 May 1993 when the Venezuelan court found 
sufficient evidence to try him for allegedly committing 
embezzlement. 
  Chamorro recently deemed the allegation that Perez 
financially supported her government "false," but she 
acknowledged the efforts of the former president to "defuse the 
spiral of warlike tension in Central America." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

