<H3> <TI>   Di Tella Announces Menem Visit to Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Di Tella Announces Menem Visit to Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1805150994 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1022 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY1805150994 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 18 May (EFE) -- Today, Argentine Foreign 
Minister Guido Di Tella announced Argentine President Carlos 
Menem's scheduled visit to Russia will take place in late 
October. 
  Di Tella, who will end his three-day visit today, pointed 
out 
that he and the Russian authorities set Menem's visit for late 
October, even though the actual date has yet to be determined. 
Di Tella is visiting Moscow at the invitation of his Russian 
counterpart, Andrey Kozyrev. 
  Di Tella, who will leave Moscow this afternoon for Buenos 
Aires, ended his stay with a lecture on the "New Argentina" at 
the Diplomatic Academy. High-ranking Russian diplomacy 
representatives, Diplomatic School students, and Latin American 
ambassadors were present at Di Tella's lecture. The foreign 
minister described a democratic and trustworthy Argentina at 
political and economic levels, an Argentina that hopes to join 
the first world. 

</TEXT>

