<F P=100> Uruguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Labor Training To Be Implemented With Germany </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Labor Training To Be Implemented With Germany </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1705142794 Montevideo LA MANANA in Spanish 13 May 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> PY1705142794 </F>
<F P=104>  Montevideo LA MANANA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Sergio Abreu and German Ambassador 
to Uruguay Ludger Buerstedde yesterday exchanged notes on the 
"implementation of a dual labor training" project. 
  The project's goal involves professional dual training 
through theoretical classes, the training of human resources 
both in our country and in Germany, and visits by German 
advisers and experts. 
  The German Government's contribution includes the 
above-mentioned experts and the required supplementary equipment 
for the existing workshops and laboratories, teaching material, 
two vehicles, and office equipment, totaling 540,000 German 
marks. The National Public Education Administration will be the 
Uruguayan counterpart for the project's implementation. 

</TEXT>

