<F P=100> Dominican Republic </F>
<H3> <TI>   Electoral Board: Balaguer Up By 1.41 Percent </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Electoral Board: Balaguer Up By 1.41 Percent </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1805150094 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1414 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1805150094 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Santo Domingo, 18 May (EFE) -- According to a 
Central Electoral Board [JCE] report, President Joaquin Balaguer 
leads opposition candidate Jose Francisco Pena Gomez by 1.41 
percent. 
  JCE Bulletin No. 14, issued after midnight last night, 
reported that Balaguer and his allies had 1,099,772 votes while 
Pena Gomez' coalition had 1,063,508. Those figures represent 
86.87 percent of the voting sites. 
  The JCE reports that Balaguer has received 42.57 percent and 
Pena Gomez has received 41.16 percent of the valid votes. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

