  [Text] Santo Domingo, 19 May (EFE) -- Dominican President 
Joaquin Balaguer has a 27,385-vote lead over Jose Francisco Pena 
Gomez in Monday's elections. This is equivalent to a 0.95 
percent lead, the Central Electoral Board (JCE) reported today. 
  JCE Bulletin No. 20 indicated that Balaguer and his allies 
have 1,222,857 votes, while the coalition that backs Pena Gomez 
has 1,195,472 votes, a difference of 27,385 votes. These 
figures correspond to the count of 96.58 percent of the 
electoral tables. Only 325 tables are pending. 
  According to the JCE bulletin, Balaguer obtained 42.36 
percent of the valid votes against Pena Gomez' 41.41 percent. 

