  [Text] Santo Domingo, 19 May (NOTIMEX) -- Tonight, Jose 
Francisco Pena Gomez, presidential candidate for the Dominican 
Revolutionary Party, PRD, demanded the annulment of the 
elections held on Monday and the holding of new elections 
because of alleged election fraud. 
  Pena Gomez made the demand before a group of diplomats and 
foreign journalists, who arrived in the Dominican Republic to 
cover the election process. The Social Democratic candidate 
said the annulment of the elections is the only way to prevent 
the Dominican masses from trying to seek a solution to the 
crisis by themselves. 

