  [Text] Havana, 14 May (PL) -- A delegation of the 
Vietnamese Communist Party Central Committee has begun an 
official visit to Cuba to exchange views and to promote even 
closer bilateral relations. 
  The delegation arrived on 13 May at the invitation of the 
Cuban Communist Party. Nguyen Van Hon, who is responsible for 
the southern provinces, is heading the delegation. 
  The Vietnamese visitors will tour agricultural, 
biotechnological, and health centers as well as the scientific 
area on the outskirts of Havana. They will also visit points of 
interest in Matanzas Province. 
  Reports indicated that the delegation will meet with 
officials of the Cuban Friendship with the Peoples Institute, 
among other organizations. 

